No one will listen when I say this, because they don't want to hear it, but I'll say it anyway. <br>
<br>
Look up pictures of explosions, dust, etc. Take them yourself if you have to, of dust not explosions, I'm not encouraging terrorism. Practice drawing those before you observe other artist's drawings. If you're really stumped, look at their stuff and see how they do it, but don't just do everything just like them. People here seem to rely too much on a stiff rigid definition of &quot;anime&quot;. You work from realism and develop a stylized version of it, you can't depend on other artist's to make every decision for you. Try to develop your own unique style. <p><table width=100% border=0>
